    {
      "name": "Explosive Tank",
      "type": "feat",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>When the guard dies, or if it rolls a 1 when checking whether its Scorchbringer action recharges, the tank on its back explodes in a 10-foot radius sphere. Each creature in that area must make a DC <span class=\"rd__dc\">12</span> Dexterity saving throw, taking 7 ([[/r 2d6]]) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The explosion ignites flammable objects that aren't being worn or carried, and it destroys the scorchbringer.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
